excerpt: Seafood eats & housemade desserts served in a casual oceanfront spot with a terrace & sunset views.
detail_description: Restaurante La Vaca Azul is a charming oceanfront spot located in the picturesque village of El Cotillo. It offers stunning sunset views from its terrace, making it an ideal place to savor delicious seafood and housemade desserts. The restaurant is known for its fresh fish and seafood rice casseroles, providing a delightful dining experience with the possibility of watching fishermen arrive with their daily catch.
name: Restaurante La Vaca Azul
address: Calle Requena, 9, 35650 El Cotillo, Las Palmas, Spain

excerpt: Seasonal tapas specialties, wines & whiskeys are offered in this warm, woodsy place with a terrace.
detail_description: La Bodega de Jandia is a cozy establishment in Morro Jable, offering a selection of seasonal small dishes, wines, and whiskeys. This charming eatery on a cobbled street specializes in country-style Canarian cuisine. Although it may be distant from Corralejo, those who venture here will be rewarded with mouthwatering local delicacies like mousse de gofio and excellent tapas.
name: La Bodega de Jandia
address: C. Diputado Manuel Velázquez Cabrera, 4, 35625 Morro Jable, Las Palmas, Spain

detail_description: Casa Santa Maria is a charming restaurant located in Betancuria, offering a delightful menu. The restaurant has garnered positive reviews for its serene and isolated ambiance, along with an intriguing interior that reflects the local heritage. Visitors have praised the helpful staff and the delicious flavors of the dishes served at Casa Santa Maria. If you're looking for a peaceful dining experience with great taste, this restaurant is worth considering during your visit to Betancuria.
name: Casa Santa Maria - Restaurant
address: C. Juan Bethencourt, 7, 35637 Betancuria, Las Palmas, Spain

excerpt: Laid-back operation with outdoor tables & a diverse menu of internationally inspired bites.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Corralejo, Citrus Surf Cafe & Bar is a delightful haven for those seeking a relaxed dining experience. Since its inception in 2008, this charming spot has become a favorite among locals and travelers alike, offering an eclectic menu that draws inspiration from global cuisines. Whether you're craving a hearty breakfast to kickstart your day or looking to unwind with friends over drinks and delicious bites after surfing, Citrus Surf Cafe caters to all tastes.
name: Citrus Surf Cafe
address: C. Anzuelo, 1, 35660 Corralejo, Las Palmas, Spain

detail_description: Azzurro Chill Out Restaurant in El Cotillo offers a sophisticated beach club atmosphere with an extensive cocktail list and delectable food menu. The seafood platter and local goat cheese board are highly recommended. It's the perfect spot for enjoying tapas and drinks, featuring market-fresh cuisine and signature tapas. Guests praise the warm welcome, attentive service, high-quality dishes, and superb cocktails. This restaurant provides a wonderful experience with innovative dishes that tantalize the taste buds.
name: Azzurro Chill Out Restaurant
address: Av. los Lagos, 1, 35650 El Cotillo, Las Palmas, Spain

detail_description: El Goloso de Cotillo is a charming French-style bakery located near the beach, offering an enticing variety of homemade pastries, cakes, sandwiches, and renowned croissants. The bakery also serves refreshing fresh juices, smoothies, and a delightful selection of ice cream. It's an ideal spot for a quick snack or leisurely lunch. Additionally, El Goloso offers freshly baked bread and ready-made sandwiches perfect for taking to the beach.
name: El Goloso de Cotillo
address: C. Pedro Cabrera Saavedra, 2, 35650 El Cotillo, Las Palmas, Spain

excerpt: Beachfront lounge offering international comfort food & cocktails, plus late-night music & dancing.
detail_description: Located in Corralejo, Waikiki Beach Club is a vibrant beachfront lounge that offers a lively atmosphere and stunning sea views. Open from 9:00 PM to 6:00 AM, it's the perfect spot for late-night entertainment with live music and dancing. The menu features international comfort food, including fresh seafood, gourmet burgers, and exotic drinks.
name: Waikiki Beach Club
address: C. de Arístides Hernández Morán, 11, 35660 Corralejo, Las Palmas, Spain

detail_description: Restaurante Los Caracolitos is located near the Salt Museum in Antigua, Las Palmas, Spain. It's a beachfront restaurant away from the typical tourist spots in Fuerteventura. The place offers quality pasta, seafood, and cocktails with a beautiful view of the beach. Visitors recommend trying their paella, shellfish soup, and fresh goat cheese as starters. The ice creams are also noteworthy for dessert.
name: Restaurante Los Caracolitos
address: Salinas del Carmen, 22, 35610 Salinas del Carmen, Las Palmas, Spain

detail_description: If you're on the hunt for authentic Canarian cuisine, look no further than Avenida Restaurante in Corralejo. This hidden gem, slightly off the beaten path, is a favorite among locals and savvy tourists alike. Known for its generous portions and freshly prepared dishes, it offers an array of traditional meals that won't break the bank. Expect to find delightful seafood options like fresh fish of the day alongside hearty meat dishes such as beef goulash and succulent steaks.
name: Avenida Restaurante
address: C. Gral. Prim, 11, 35660 Corralejo, Las Palmas, Spain

excerpt: Comfort food, hot breakfast & cocktails served in an informal venue with a terrace & ocean views.
name: Restaurante Cantante Café
address: C. P.º Atlántico, 2, 35660 Corralejo, Las Palmas, Spain

detail_description: The Ugly Duckling in Corralejo is a cozy Scandinavian-international restaurant known for its diverse culinary offerings. The Danish-owned gem serves up Nordic delights and international favorites, such as tender duck breast with whiskey and tarragon sauce, rich beef tenderloin with creamy mashed potatoes, and prawns in fragrant dill sauce. Situated in the old part of Corralejo, this small restaurant has gained recognition for its quality food and exceptional service.
name: The Ugly Duckling
address: C. Abubilla, 1, 35660 Corralejo, Las Palmas, Spain

detail_description: La Arroceria is a restaurant located in Corralejo, Fuerteventura, offering traditional rice and paella dishes from Alicante and Valencia. The menu includes a variety of options accompanied by the best Mediterranean wine, fish, and meats. Despite some concerns about timing and ventilation, visitors praise the delicious paella made with fresh ingredients. The friendly staff and great ambiance add to the overall dining experience at La Arroceria.
name: La arroceria
address: Detrás del hiperdino, C. Pejín, 10, 35660 Corralejo, Las Palmas, Spain

excerpt: An array of juices, plus vegan burgers, sandwiches & cakes, in a snug space with a leafy terrace.
detail_description: Nestled in the vibrant surf town of Corralejo on Fuerteventura's northern coast, H2O Juice Bar & Vegan Café is a delightful sanctuary for health enthusiasts and food lovers alike. This charming vegan café specializes in an impressive selection of fresh juices and smoothies, alongside a diverse menu that caters to all tastes. From hearty breakfast options like waffles and muffins to savory lunch dishes including salads, sandwiches, bowls, and burgers, there's something for everyone here.
name: H2O Juice Bar & Vegan Cafè
address: C. la Milagrosa, 29, 35660 Corralejo, Las Palmas, Spain

detail_description: RESTAURANTE EL ROQUE LOS PESCADORES is a renowned fish restaurant in El Cotillo, offering stunning sea views and excellent dishes made with fresh fish and shellfish. The terrace provides a panoramic view of the Southern beach area, making it an ideal spot to witness breathtaking sunsets. Located on the northwest coast of Fuerteventura, this restaurant is known for its Canarian charm and is highly recommended for a leisurely lunch while exploring the area.
name: RESTAURANTE EL ROQUE LOS PESCADORES
address: C. la Caleta, 73, 35650 El Cotillo, Las Palmas, Spain

detail_description: Restaurante Happy Cactus El Cotillo is a completely vegan restaurant located in the harbor area, featuring a small Veg-Shop. The daily changing menu offers Italian-inspired dishes, baked goods, desserts, and beverages such as salads, gluten-free pasta in tomato sauce, seitan-vegetable stew, veggie burger, Happy Bowl with coconut rice and tofu. Additionally, they serve banana bread, carrot and raspberry cakes along with freshly prepared juices and smoothies.
name: Restaurante Happy Cactus El Cotillo - Vegan Food
address: Av. los Lagos, 42, Local 3 Edificio, 35650 Marfolin, Las Palmas, Spain

detail_description: Nestled in an old restored Canary Island house near Corralejo, El Moral Restaurant offers a unique dining experience with traditional Canary Island dishes infused with haute cuisine. The charming atmosphere and carefully crafted details create a magical ambiance that envelops visitors as soon as they step in. The restaurant is known for its excellent food, including exquisite goat dishes and off-menu options. With the option of half portions, guests can sample a wide range of dishes while enjoying the delightful wine selection.
name: El Moral Restaurant
address: Ctra. del Centro, 94, 35640 La Oliva, Las Palmas, Spain

detail_description: Restaurante La Frasquita is a historic restaurant in Caleta de Fuste, Fuerteventura, with a rich legacy as the first restaurant in the area before it became a tourist destination. Rebuilt and reopened in 2017, it continues to maintain its original essence.
name: Restaurante La Frasquita - Fuerteventura
address: C. Pitera, s/n, 35610 Castillo Caleta de Fuste, Las Palmas, Spain

name: La Barraca
address: C. Isidro Díaz, 14, 35629 Tarajalejo, Las Palmas, Spain

detail_description: Casa de comidas Valtarajal is a restaurant in Betancuria, Spain, offering typical local dishes such as goat stew, ropavieja, and cheese boards. The restaurant provides a friendly service and also offers children's dishes. The name 'Valtarajal' may be derived from the first defensive tower built by Normans in Butancuria. Visitors recommend trying the goat stew available only on weekends and praise the delicious traditional food with good prices.
name: Casa de comidas Valtarajal
address: C. Roberto Roldán, 23, 35637 Betancuria, Las Palmas, Spain

detail_description: Rojo Tomate - Pizzeria Lajares is a renowned pizza establishment that definitely lives up to expectations. They serve delicious pizzas with a wide variety of toppings, ensuring there's something to please every taste. The antipasti is particularly noteworthy, offering original and muy rico options. Gracias! In Fuerteventura, Italian food is a must as the island has a significant Italian population.
name: Rojo Tomate - Pizzeria Lajares
address: C. la Cancela, 8, 35650 La Oliva, Las Palmas, Spain

detail_description: Restaurante Mahoh is located in a charming early 19th-century rural abode and takes its name from an old aboriginal word meaning 'land, country.' The restaurant is associated with an environmental group dedicated to preserving Fuerteventura's landscape. Owned by Tinin Martinez, it's a family affair with his son-in-law Victor Curbelo serving as the maitre d'hotel. The restaurant offers a rustic farmhouse setting where traditional Canary Island dishes are served.
name: Restaurante Mahoh
address: sitio de Juan Bello, S/n, 35640 Villaverde, Las Palmas, Spain

detail_description: El Sombrero is a Mexican restaurant situated in the vibrant Corralejo. The menu boasts an array of classic Mexican fare, including tacos, burritos, and fajitas, complemented by a selection of cocktails and margaritas. Visitors have praised the attentive service and knowledgeable staff. The restaurant offers delectable hanging kebabs with optional sides to customize your meal. Guests can also savor sangria while admiring the stunning sunset over the shore.
name: El Sombrero
address: C. Marítima, 4, 35660 Corralejo, Las Palmas, Spain

detail_description: Flip-Flops Beach Cafe is a charming bistro located in Pozo Negro, offering a picturesque first-row sea view. Run by Geoff and Teresa, the cafe provides a tranquil setting where visitors can savor tapas, fresh fish, paella, and delightful sweet and savory crepes. The English couple who recently took over the cafe ensure generous portions of tasty food with cold beers while overlooking Pozo Negro beach.
name: Flip-Flops Beach Cafe
address: Diseminado Pozo Negro, 24, 35639 Antigua, Las Palmas, Spain

detail_description: Restaurante La Marisma de Mariquita Hierro is a stylish restaurant with a prime location overlooking the sea. It boasts a beautiful seaside view from its dining room and rooftop terrace, offering wonderful sunset views. The restaurant is known for having the longest list of Canarian wines in town. While some guests have experienced slow service and language barriers, many praise the delicious food, particularly recommending the chateaubriand for two and seafood options.
name: Restaurante La Marisma de Mariquita Hierro
address: C. Santiago Hierro, s/n, 35650 El Cotillo, Las Palmas, Spain

detail_description: La Tasca de Raíces is a tranquil oasis in the heart of Pajara, offering a reduced but refined menu with dishes of great finesse. The restaurant's patio provides a peaceful setting to savor delicious food and enjoy a selection of wines by the glass. Guests praise the tasteful and well-prepared food, excellent service, and fair prices. With its beautiful decor and beachfront location, this restaurant is highly recommended for those seeking an exceptional dining experience in Fuerteventura.
name: La Tasca de Raíces | Spanish Tapas & Local Food
address: C. Matías López, 7, 35620 Gran Tarajal, Las Palmas, Spain

excerpt: Mediterranean fare with a seafood emphasis served in polished waterside surrounds with a terrace.
detail_description: Restaurante La Marquesina is a delightful culinary gem nestled by the shimmering waters of Corralejo, Fuerteventura. This charming eatery specializes in Mediterranean cuisine with a strong focus on seafood, offering an array of dishes that include traditional paella and fresh fish soup. Diners can enjoy their meals on the lovely terrace while soaking in stunning sea views. Although some guests have noted delays during busy times and occasional discomfort from kitchen fumes, many rave about the quality of food and friendly service.
name: Restaurante La Marquesina
address: Av. Marítima, 35660 Corralejo, Las Palmas, Spain

detail_description: Hamburguesería Single Fin is a must-visit spot in Corralejo, offering a variety of mouth-watering burgers, including vegan options made from ingredients like Tempeh, Tofu, and chickpeas. The laid-back surfer atmosphere adds to the charm of this place. Visitors praise the friendly staff and quick service. They also make their own bread with several varieties available. Additionally, they offer craft beers that are highly recommended.
name: Hamburguesería Single Fin
address: Calle Hernán Cortés, 2, 35660 Corralejo, Las Palmas, Spain

excerpt: Well-known fast-food chain serving grilled burgers, fries & shakes.
name: Burger King
address: Av. Ntra. Sra. del Carmen, 35660 Fuerteventura, Las Palmas, Spain

detail_description: La Playita is a highly recommended restaurant known for its finest grilled fish and seafood, offering the best scenery right opposite the ocean. The prices are reasonable with available offers, making it a great dining experience. The staff is professional, friendly, and very attentive to ensure guests have a wonderful time. Additionally, the restaurant is well-positioned and welcoming to families with generous portions of delicious food.
name: La Playita
address: Av. Marítima, 28, 35660 Corralejo, Las Palmas, Spain

detail_description: El Toro Bravo is a steak house with a focus on meat. It has been open for 12 years and is popular for its tender grilled meats. The menu has aromas of Chateaubriand and T-bone competing, prepared with great expertise. Fish and spectacular brochettes are also available on the menu.
name: Restaurante El Toro Bravo
address: Av. Ntra. Sra. del Carmen, 22, 35660 Corralejo, Las Palmas, Spain

name: La Mamma Pastas & Grill
address: C. Anzuelo, 5, 35660 Corralejo, Las Palmas, Spain

detail_description: Restaurante Gregorio El Pescador is a relaxed yet upscale dining spot located in the old town, nestled in a car-free alley near the harbor. The family-owned establishment has been serving fresh seafood for years, carrying on the legacy of its founder, Gregorio, who was a local fisherman. With both indoor and outdoor seating available, patrons can enjoy live sports on TV while savoring their meals during the day and revel in evening entertainment at night.
name: Restaurante Gregorio El Pescador
address: Calle Iglesia, 11, 35660 Corralejo, Las Palmas, Spain

excerpt: Locally caught fish in a bright stop decorated in blue & white hues, plus a terrace with sea views.
detail_description: Restaurante La Farola del Mar is a charming eatery located near La Laja, at the end of Matorral Beach in Morro Jable, Fuerteventura. The restaurant boasts a tranquil ambiance and offers breathtaking views of the clear turquoise waters. It's one of the oldest dining establishments in Morro Jable and sits right on a small beach with a staircase leading to the sea for those who want to take a dip in the Atlantic before or after their meal.
name: Restaurante La Farola del Mar
address: Avenida del Mar, S/N, 35625 Morro Jable, Las Palmas, Spain

detail_description: Sanus Fuerteventura is a top choice for those seeking gluten-free and vegetarian dining options in Corralejo. The restaurant offers a wide range of gluten-free, vegan, and vegetarian dishes from Italian, Spanish, and Mediterranean cuisines. Visitors with dietary restrictions can enjoy a diverse menu that includes options like spicy penne with seafood. The attentive staff are known for their passion for the food they serve, making it an excellent spot for lunch or dinner in Fuerteventura.
name: Sanus Fuerteventura
address: C. Anzuelo, 4, 35660 Corralejo, Las Palmas, Spain

excerpt: Traditional Italian restaurant serving up authentic dishes in a compact, laid-back spot.
detail_description: Nestled in a cozy corner, Restaurante Da Uli is a charming Italian eatery that captures the essence of authentic cuisine. This laid-back spot is perfect for surfers and water sports enthusiasts looking to refuel after an exhilarating day on the waves. With hearty portions and delicious homemade pasta, it’s no wonder visitors rave about their experiences here. The friendly staff goes above and beyond to ensure you feel at home, making every meal memorable.
name: Restaurante Da Uli
address: C. José Segura Torres, 9, 35660 Corralejo, Las Palmas, Spain

excerpt: Tapas tasting trays & Mediterranean dishes, plus Spanish wines, at a slick gastropub with a terrace.
detail_description: Land of Freedom restaurante y tapas bar is a newly established eatery in Fuerteventura, offering a diverse menu with Mediterranean dishes and Spanish wines. The restaurant prides itself on its commitment to the slow-food philosophy and offers an array of tasting trays, including gluten-free options. Situated in a serene square in Corralejo, the restaurant provides a tranquil ambiance for patrons to savor their meals.
name: Land of Freedom restaurante y tapas bar
address: cc Lobos Bahia, Av. Ntra. Sra. del Carmen, 33, 35660 Corralejo, Las Palmas, Spain

detail_description: InFusion, a Louisiana-inspired restaurant, comes highly recommended for those seeking authentic Cajun and Creole cuisine. Other top suggestions include Casa Manola and Avenida for genuine Spanish dishes, as well as Fadus for the finest steaks. For first-time visitors, InFusion offers a delightful experience with its mouthwatering food options such as beef bourguignon served alongside fluffy mashed potatoes and vegetables.
name: InFusion - Louisiana Restaurant
address: C. María González Carballo, 21, 35660 Corralejo, Las Palmas, Spain

detail_description: Antiguo Café del Puerto is a charming waterfront spot with friendly and attentive staff. It offers a diverse selection of over 50 tapas, flavorful paella, and a variety of wines. Guests can also enjoy a relaxing cortado while taking in the lovely view of the nearby harbor and Isla de Lobos in the background. The cozy interior provides a warm atmosphere, while outdoor seating is available for those who prefer to dine al fresco.
name: Antiguo Café del Puerto
address: C. la Ballena, 10, 35660 Corralejo, Las Palmas, Spain

detail_description: Indian Tandoori Spices Corralejo is a top-notch Indian restaurant that offers an extensive menu of authentic and delicious Indian cuisine. The restaurant boasts a clean and welcoming environment, with friendly staff who provide excellent service. Customers have raved about the quality of the food, highlighting dishes such as lamb achaari and saag paneer as particularly outstanding. The establishment is known for its fresh ingredients, homemade dishes, and generous portions.
name: Indian Tandoori Spices Corralejo
address: Av. Ntra. Sra. del Carmen, 64, 35660 Corralejo, Las Palmas, Spain

excerpt: Unique, seasonal vegan dishes, juices & desserts in a rustic, homey place with a sustainable focus.
detail_description: Nestled in the charming town of Corralejo, Baobab stands as Fuerteventura's oldest vegan restaurant, having opened its doors back in July 2014. This beloved eatery is renowned for its unique and seasonal vegan dishes that celebrate sustainability. The rustic ambiance creates a warm and inviting atmosphere where guests can indulge in an array of delightful options, from hearty vegan burgers to refreshing summer rolls and both sweet and savory pastries.
name: Baobab
address: C. José Segura Torres, 14, 35660 Corralejo, Las Palmas, Spain

name: Restaurante Avenida del Mar
address: Av. Tomás Grau Gurrea, 1, 35625 Morro Jable, Las Palmas, Spain

detail_description: Olivo Corso is a popular Spanish and Mediterranean restaurant in El Cotillo, known for its authentic and fresh dishes that even locals love. The cozy and beautiful decor adds to the ambiance, making it an ideal spot for lunch on the way to the beach or drinks after a day of sun and sand. The restaurant offers amazing octopus and super fresh tuna tataki, with a sister location near the new harbor.
name: Olivo Corso
address: C. Mallorquin, 34, 35650 El Cotillo, Las Palmas, Spain

detail_description: Restaurante El Horno is a rustic gem located in Villaverde, Fuerteventura. This hidden culinary treasure offers authentic local cuisine at great value. The restaurant serves a variety of typical Canary Island dishes, including highly recommended roast goat meat and mouthwatering desserts. With its friendly staff and relaxed atmosphere, it provides a welcoming dining experience for both locals and visitors.
name: Restaurante El Horno
address: Carretera general, 44, 35640 Villaverde, Las Palmas, Spain

detail_description: "That's Amore" is a cozy café located in a great spot, perfect for enjoying a drink, snack, or cake. They offer delicious breakfast options and take-away service. The café serves Italian standard coffee with good barista art and also offers a variety of ice cream flavors at reasonable prices. Guests can savor their lovely cafe con leche and breakfast toast with jam in the relaxing ambiance.
name: That's Amore
address: Av. Ntra. Sra. del Carmen, 42, 35660 Corralejo, Las Palmas, Spain

excerpt: International flavors & fine wines in an elegant, wood-beamed room or on a shaded terrace.
detail_description: Restaurante Marabú is a spacious and elegant restaurant located on the southern side of the island. It offers an inviting atmosphere with a beautiful shaded garden, traditional ambiance, and contemporary international cuisine alongside typical Canarian dishes and seafood. The restaurant's charming garden is surrounded by a volcanic stone wall, palm trees, and wine barrels, providing a delightful setting for dining day or night.
name: Restaurante Marabú
address: C. Fuente de Hija, 2, 35626 Esquinzo, Las Palmas, Spain

detail_description: Restaurante Cangrejo Colorao is a charming spot offering delicious French tarts and bocadillos. The portions are generous, and the prices are reasonable, including drinks. The staff is friendly, making it a great place to enjoy fresh fish and seafood dishes. While the traditional rice was missing from the seafood paella, it was rich in flavor with an abundance of fish, mussels, and shrimp.
name: Restaurante Cangrejo Colorao
address: Calle De, C. Juan Ramón Jiménez, 1, 35600 Las Palmas, Spain

detail_description: Nestor's Restaurant & Steakhouse is a hidden gem on the resort, offering a special dining experience that's well worth seeking out. It's advisable to make a reservation and consider taking a taxi to get there. The restaurant offers excellent service and food, with generous portions such as the mix grill that may require sharing. Booking in advance is recommended due to its popularity.
name: Nestor's Restaurant & Steakhouse
address: C. El Greco, s/n, 35610 Castillo Caleta de Fuste, Las Palmas, Spain

detail_description: El Faro Lounge Bar is a lovely establishment with a stunning setting, offering great views of the bay and marina. It's the perfect spot to enjoy cocktails while watching the mesmerizing sunset. The bar offers beautiful and worth-every-cent cocktails like Martini Espresso and 'Sex on the beach'. While the staff might be a bit slow, it's an ideal place to chill out with some chilled-out sounds from the DJ.
name: El Faro Lounge Bar
address: C. Tenerife, s/n, 35610 Castillo Caleta de Fuste, Las Palmas, Spain

name: Las Cazuelitas, El Cotillo
address: Av. los Lagos, 42, 35650 El Cotillo, Las Palmas, Spain

detail_description: La Ballena El Cotillo is a popular cocktail bar and eatery with stunning views of the cliffs in the south side of town, making it a favorite spot for surfers. The menu features fantastic Canarian seafood and great deals on long drinks. Visitors praise the delicious food, including desserts and wines, as well as the exceptional service provided by staff members like Frederick, Lazaro, and Fabio.
name: La Ballena El Cotillo
address: C. Pinito del Oro, 1, 3, 35650 El Cotillo, Las Palmas, Spain
